{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01DhbuMmzk9PTfZCR234EwrL","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `repository-s3` plugin IS installed (it's in the plugins directory). The cluster is green with 3 nodes. Now I need to:\n\n1. Create the `es-secure-settings` secret with MinIO credentials (access key and secret key)\n2. Add these credentials to the Elasticsearch keystore on all 3 nodes\n3. Register the snapshot repository\n4. Create a snapshot\n\nThe MinIO credentials are:\n- Access Key: `minioadmin`\n- Secret Key: `minioadmin`\n\nFor Elasticsearch's S3 repository, the keystore settings needed are:\n- `s3.client.default.access_key` = `minioadmin`\n- `s3.client.default.secret_key` = `minioadmin`\n\nI need to create the `es-secure-settings` secret with these credentials, then add them to the keystore on each node using `elasticsearch-keystore add`, call `_nodes/reload_secure_settings` to reload without restarting, and finally register the snapshot repository.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1936,"cache_read_input_tokens":33227,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1936},"output_tokens":28,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6ec167db-b949-4c0b-8565-825d3a50d108","uuid":"0f6312e0-ba76-4c51-81db-70942181b7c7","request_id":"req_011CccHGVJUJunUrbB4q6h9y"}
