{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01DxEzdW8FMn285XaPaNK3CT","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is complete and verified. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n**Problem:** The `minio` Kubernetes Service didn't exist (causing DNS failures in the init job), the `es-backups` bucket was never created, and the Elasticsearch keystore had no S3 credentials.\n\n**Steps taken:**\n\n1. **Retrieved MinIO credentials** from the `minio-root` secret (`minioadmin`/`minioadmin`).\n\n2. **Created `es-secure-settings` secret** with the S3 keystore keys:\n   ```\n   s3.client.default.access_key = minioadmin\n   s3.client.default.secret_key = minioadmin\n   ```\n\n3. **Added credentials to the ES keystore** on all 3 nodes via `elasticsearch-keystore add --stdin` (credentials stored only in the keystore, not in `elasticsearch.yml` or env vars).\n\n4. **Reloaded secure settings** via `POST /_nodes/reload_secure_settings` — all 3 nodes succeeded, no pod restarts needed.\n\n5. **Created the `minio` ClusterIP Service** (was missing — the init job failed to create the bucket because DNS couldn't resolve `minio.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local`).\n\n6. **Created the `es-backups` bucket** in MinIO using `mc mb`.\n\n7. **Registered `minio-repo`** snapshot repository (type `s3`, path-style access, HTTP protocol).\n\n8. **Snapshot `snapshot-1`** completed with `SUCCESS` — 1 shard backed up, 0 failures, data files confirmed in MinIO."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1176,"cache_read_input_tokens":48716,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1176},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6ec167db-b949-4c0b-8565-825d3a50d108","uuid":"de8e61b9-7148-4dc3-a868-a17dee91fb87","request_